## **What Is an Emerald Cut Diamond? The Complete Definition**

**An emerald cut diamond is a rectangular step-cut diamond with clipped corners, featuring long parallel facets arranged in descending "steps" from the table facet down the pavilion — producing the distinctive hall-of-mirrors optical effect.**

The name "emerald cut" comes from its origin in gemstone cutting — the rectangular step-cut was developed specifically for emerald gemstones to reduce the mechanical stress of cutting and minimize chip risk on a brittle stone.

When applied to diamonds, the same rectangular step-cut architecture produces an entirely different aesthetic from brilliant cuts — broad, sweeping flashes of light rather than rapid, complex scintillation.

