" rel="noopener noreferrer">$19,060</a></strong></td><td><strong>8/10 — The Collection Masterpiece.</strong> Approaching $20k due to the absolute colorless "D" designation. For an emerald cut of this size, the step facets will look remarkably like pure, clean ice. It carries a heavy color tax, but it's a stellar elite spec.</td></tr><tr class="highlight-row"><td><strong>1.62ct</strong></td><td>G-VS1 Ideal</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27154101?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">$13,690</a></strong></td><td><strong>10/10 — The Carat/Value Pivot.</strong> Brilliant pricing structure. You are getting an extra 12 points of diamond weight over the 1.50ct stone, yet you are saving $1,200 in cold cash. The G-VS1 setup will easily remain eye-clean and face up bright white. Buy this over the 1.50ct.</td></tr><tr class="highlight-row"><td><strong>1.80ct</strong></td><td>F-VS1 Ideal</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/18652618?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">$18,450</a></strong></td><td><strong>9/10 — The "Almost 2 Carat" Stealth Play.</strong> For less than the price of the 1.54ct D-color stone, you get a massive jump in surface area footprint. Sitting at 1.80ct lets you bypass the brutal 2.00-carat pricing cliff while maintaining premium F color and flawless eye-clarity.</td></tr></tbody></table>

**The "magic size" insight at 1.5ct:** A 1.62ct G-VS1 at $13,690 costs $1,200 less than a 1.50ct G-VS1 at $14,890. The 1.50ct stone carries a "round carat weight" premium — buyers searching for "1.5 carat" diamonds pay a premium for hitting the psychologically significant number.

The 1.62ct delivers more diamond for less money. This is identical to the magic number phenomenon documented in the **[diamond prices guide](https://diamondcritics.com/diamond-prices/)**.

