reign Spec.</strong> Pushes past the 5.10ct competitor with GCAL credentials. It represents absolute lab-grown perfection, though it requires a top-tier budget to match the pedigree.</td></tr><tr class="highlight-row"><td>GIA</td><td><strong>5.40ct</strong></td><td>D-FL</td><td>Ideal</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27423677?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">$58,990</a></strong></td><td><strong>6/10 — The GIA Status Tax.</strong> A massive $58.9k price point. GIA has recently scaled up its lab-grown dossier tiering, resulting in an enormous premium over IGI and GCAL for the exact same physical and optical properties. Only for collectors who demand the GIA logo on their documentation.</td></tr></tbody></table>

