d><strong>3.09ct</strong> F-VS1 vs <strong>4.62ct</strong> D-IF</td><td>$63,580</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27465161?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">$19,640</a></strong></td><td><strong>$43,940</strong></td><td><strong>10/10 — Ultimate Capital Efficiency.</strong> A massive $43k savings that could fund an entire high-end jewelry suite. Moving from a 3-carat near-colorless natural stone to a near 5-carat absolute colorless D-IF masterpiece is an unassailable value play.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>5ct</strong> D-VS1 vs <strong>5ct</strong> D-IF</td><td>$121,480</td><td><strong><a href="https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27423440?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&amp;a_cid=55e51e63&amp;chan=blog-informational" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">$20,920</a></strong></td><td><strong>$100,560</strong></td><td><strong>10/10 — Six-Figure Sovereign Win.</strong> Saving six figures ($100k+) on a matching carat setup is the definitive mic-drop for lab-grown material. You maximize clarity to Internally Flawless for an 83% discount off the earth-mined structural equivalent.</td></tr></tbody></table>

The emerald cut lab-grown arbitrage is the most compelling in the entire diamond market at 2ct+ sizes. A natural 2ct E-VVS2 at $25,480 versus a lab-grown 2.23ct D-IF at $4,960 — $20,520 saved for better specs and more carat weight. At 5ct, the gap is $100,560 for identical visual result.

As documented in the **[lab-grown vs natural diamond price guide](https://diamondcritics.com/lab-grown-vs-natural-diamond-price/)**, lab prices have collapsed 68% since 2020.

> 
> 
> "A 2ct natural emerald cut E-VVS2 at $25,480. A 2.23ct lab-grown D-IF at $4,960. You save $20,520, gain 0.23ct of physical length on an already elongated shape, get better color (D vs E) and better clarity (IF vs VVS2). The emerald cut's open step-cut facets amplify every quality advantage — including the advantage of spending $20,000 less on an identical-looking stone." — Farzana Hasan
> 
