 discount compared to the premium emerald profile for equal carat weight.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Durability</strong></td><td>Good — clipped corners</td><td>Excellent — rounded corners</td><td><strong>Cushion</strong></td><td><strong>9/10 — Peak Structural Integrity.</strong> While the emerald cut’s mitered corners are far more secure than the sharp, brittle points of a princess cut, it still features exposed straight edges. The cushion’s continuous, gently curved pillow perimeter completely redistributes external forces, making it practically immune to daily chipping.</td></tr><tr class="highlight-row"><td><strong>Trending in 2026</strong></td><td>Stable</td><td>Growing (elongated antique)</td><td><strong>Cushion</strong></td><td><strong>9/10 — The Elongated Evolution.</strong> While the classic square cushion remains an iconic staple, the May 2026 market is seeing massive demand for elongated antique cushion cuts. They successfully capture the sleek, finger-lengthening look traditionally reserved for emeralds, but with high-octane brilliant fire.</td></tr></tbody></table>

